Rub salt and pepper onto the pork belly slices.

Heat cooking oil in a deep pan or pot. Fry the pork belly slices until crispy and golden brown. Set aside on a paper towel to drain excess oil.

For the Kare-Kare:

In a separate pot, sautÃ© the garlic and onions until fragrant.

Add the pre-boiled oxtail and tripe to the pot. Cook for a few minutes.

Dilute the peanut butter in the broth and pour it into the pot.

Add the ground peanuts and annatto powder. Stir well.

Allow the mixture to simmer until it thickens. If it becomes too thick, you can add more broth.

Add the sliced eggplants, string beans, and banana hearts. Cook until the vegetables are tender.

Season the kare-kare with fish sauce or salt to taste.

To serve, arrange the crispy bagnet on a plate and pour the kare-kare sauce and vegetables over it.

Serve hot with shrimp paste on the side."
